{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":458,"text":"I think it's safe to say"},{"time":2276,"text":"that all humans will be intimate with death"},{"time":6260,"text":"at least once in their lives."},{"time":9100,"text":"But what if that intimacy began"},{"time":11117,"text":"long before you faced your own transition"},{"time":13406,"text":"from life into death?"},{"time":16200,"text":"What would life be like"},{"time":18129,"text":"if the dead literally lived alongside you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":21725,"text":"In my husband's homeland"},{"time":23651,"text":"in the highlands of Sulawesi island"},{"time":26331,"text":"in eastern Indonesia,"},{"time":28358,"text":"there is a community of people that experience death"},{"time":30827,"text":"not as a singular event"},{"time":33448,"text":"but as a gradual social process."},{"time":37200,"text":"In Tana Toraja,"},{"time":38997,"text":"the most important social moments in people's lives,"},{"time":42035,"text":"the focal points of social and cultural interaction"},{"time":45381,"text":"are not weddings or births or even family dinners,"},{"time":50096,"text":"but funerals."},{"time":52590,"text":"So these funerals are characterized"},{"time":54919,"text":"by elaborate rituals"},{"time":56830,"text":"that tie people in a system of reciprocal debt"},{"time":60345,"text":"based on the amount of animals --"},{"time":62482,"text":"pigs, chickens and, most importantly, water buffalo --"},{"time":67476,"text":"that are sacrificed and distributed"},{"time":70159,"text":"in the name of the deceased."},{"time":72926,"text":"So this cultural complex surrounding death,"},{"time":76663,"text":"the ritual enactment of the end of life,"},{"time":80291,"text":"has made death the most visible"},{"time":82871,"text":"and remarkable aspect of Toraja's landscape."},{"time":87700,"text":"Lasting anywhere from a few days"},{"time":90128,"text":"to a few weeks,"},{"time":91968,"text":"funeral ceremonies are a raucous affair,"},{"time":95110,"text":"where commemorating someone who's died"},{"time":98152,"text":"is not so much a private sadness"},{"time":100743,"text":"but more of a publicly shared transition."},{"time":105811,"text":"And it's a transition that's just as much"},{"time":108212,"text":"about the identity of the living"},{"time":110414,"text":"as it is about remembrance of the dead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114227,"text":"So every year, thousands of visitors"},{"time":116721,"text":"come to Tana Toraja to see, as it were,"},{"time":119285,"text":"this culture of death,"},{"time":121349,"text":"and for many people these grandiose ceremonies"},{"time":124935,"text":"and the length of the ceremonies"},{"time":127693,"text":"are somehow incommensurable"},{"time":130437,"text":"with the way that we face our own mortality in the West."},{"time":135360,"text":"So even as we share death as a universal experience,"},{"time":141274,"text":"it's not experienced the same way the world over."},{"time":145416,"text":"And as an anthropologist,"},{"time":147684,"text":"I see these differences in experience"},{"time":150146,"text":"being rooted in the cultural and social world"},{"time":154895,"text":"through which we define the phenomena around us."},{"time":160071,"text":"So where we see an unquestionable reality,"},{"time":164956,"text":"death as an irrefutable biological condition,"},{"time":169879,"text":"Torajans see the expired corporeal form"},{"time":173184,"text":"as part of a larger social genesis."},{"time":176996,"text":"So again, the physical cessation of life"},{"time":181792,"text":"is not the same as death."},{"time":184741,"text":"In fact, a member of society is only truly dead"},{"time":188324,"text":"when the extended family can agree upon"},{"time":191758,"text":"and marshal the resources necessary"},{"time":194102,"text":"to hold a funeral ceremony"},{"time":195888,"text":"that is considered appropriate in terms of resources"},{"time":199540,"text":"for the status of the deceased."},{"time":202235,"text":"And this ceremony has to take place"},{"time":204507,"text":"in front of the eyes of the whole community"},{"time":206669,"text":"with everyone's participation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209276,"text":"So after a person's physical death,"},{"time":212146,"text":"their body is placed in a special room"},{"time":214885,"text":"in the traditional residence, which is called the tongkonan."},{"time":217941,"text":"And the tongkonan is symbolic"},{"time":220089,"text":"not only of the family's identity"},{"time":224191,"text":"but also of the human life cycle from birth to death."},{"time":227888,"text":"So essentially, the shape of the building"},{"time":229787,"text":"that you're born into is the shape"},{"time":231831,"text":"of the structure which carries you"},{"time":233725,"text":"to your ancestral resting place."},{"time":237421,"text":"Until the funeral ceremony,"},{"time":239701,"text":"which can be held years after a person's physical death,"},{"time":244648,"text":"the deceased is referred to as \"to makala,\" a sick person,"},{"time":250363,"text":"or \"to mama,\" a person who is asleep,"},{"time":254706,"text":"and they continue to be a member of the household."},{"time":258489,"text":"They are symbolically fed and cared for,"},{"time":261848,"text":"and the family at this time"},{"time":263730,"text":"will begin a number of ritual injunctions,"},{"time":266643,"text":"which communicates to the wider community around them"},{"time":269605,"text":"that one of their members is undergoing the transition"},{"time":272427,"text":"from this life into the afterlife"},{"time":275462,"text":"known as Puya."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277722,"text":"So I know what some of you must be thinking right now."},{"time":280444,"text":"Is she really saying that these people live"},{"time":283220,"text":"with the bodies of their dead relatives?"},{"time":286288,"text":"And that's exactly what I'm saying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289360,"text":"But instead of giving in to the sort of visceral reaction"},{"time":292840,"text":"we have to this idea of proximity to bodies,"},{"time":296378,"text":"proximity to death,"},{"time":298512,"text":"or how this notion just does not fit"},{"time":301032,"text":"into our very biological or medical"},{"time":304284,"text":"sort of definition of death,"},{"time":307088,"text":"I like to think about what the Torajan way"},{"time":310175,"text":"of viewing death encompasses of the human experience"},{"time":314931,"text":"that the medical definition leaves out."},{"time":319964,"text":"I think that Torajans socially recognize"},{"time":323705,"text":"and culturally express"},{"time":326835,"text":"what many of us feel to be true"},{"time":329297,"text":"despite the widespread acceptance"},{"time":331721,"text":"of the biomedical definition of death,"},{"time":336468,"text":"and that is that our relationships with other humans,"},{"time":340363,"text":"their impact on our social reality,"},{"time":343869,"text":"doesn't cease with the termination"},{"time":346345,"text":"of the physical processes of the body,"},{"time":350326,"text":"that there's a period of transition"},{"time":352969,"text":"as the relationship between the living and the dead"},{"time":357190,"text":"is transformed but not ended."},{"time":362043,"text":"So Torajans express this idea of this enduring relationship"},{"time":366881,"text":"by lavishing love and attention"},{"time":368723,"text":"on the most visible symbol of that relationship,"},{"time":371993,"text":"the human body."},{"time":373770,"text":"So my husband has fond memories"},{"time":376594,"text":"of talking to and playing with"},{"time":379140,"text":"and generally being around his deceased grandfather,"},{"time":382601,"text":"and for him there is nothing unnatural about this."},{"time":385876,"text":"This is a natural part of the process"},{"time":388805,"text":"as the family comes to terms with the transition"},{"time":392274,"text":"in their relationship to the deceased,"},{"time":394966,"text":"and this is the transition from relating to the deceased"},{"time":397455,"text":"as a person who's living"},{"time":399725,"text":"to relating to the deceased"},{"time":401627,"text":"as a person who's an ancestor."},{"time":403453,"text":"And here you can see these wooden effigies"},{"time":405638,"text":"of the ancestors,"},{"time":406841,"text":"so these are people who have already been buried,"},{"time":408432,"text":"already had a funeral ceremony."},{"time":409898,"text":"These are called tau tau."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412808,"text":"So the funeral ceremony itself"},{"time":415328,"text":"embodies this relational perspective on death."},{"time":419224,"text":"It ritualizes the impact of death on families"},{"time":423607,"text":"and communities."},{"time":425830,"text":"And it's also a moment of self-awareness."},{"time":428998,"text":"It's a moment when people think about who they are,"},{"time":432127,"text":"their place in society,"},{"time":435632,"text":"and their role in the life cycle"},{"time":437935,"text":"in accordance with Torajan cosmology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442128,"text":"There's a saying in Toraja"},{"time":443782,"text":"that all people will become grandparents,"},{"time":446916,"text":"and what this means is that after death,"},{"time":449297,"text":"we all become part of the ancestral line"},{"time":452146,"text":"that anchors us between the past and the present"},{"time":455954,"text":"and will define who our loved ones are into the future."},{"time":460943,"text":"So essentially, we all become grandparents"},{"time":463732,"text":"to the generations of human children"},{"time":466146,"text":"that come after us."},{"time":469160,"text":"And this metaphor of membership"},{"time":471389,"text":"in the greater human family"},{"time":473519,"text":"is the way that children also describe"},{"time":475364,"text":"the money that they invest"},{"time":476942,"text":"in these sacrificial buffaloes"},{"time":478913,"text":"that are thought to carry people's soul"},{"time":480955,"text":"from here to the afterlife,"},{"time":483125,"text":"and children will explain"},{"time":484711,"text":"that they will invest the money in this"},{"time":487290,"text":"because they want to repay their parents"},{"time":489717,"text":"the debt for all of the years their parents spent"},{"time":492962,"text":"investing and caring for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495476,"text":"But the sacrifice of buffalo"},{"time":498186,"text":"and the ritual display of wealth"},{"time":500873,"text":"also exhibits the status of the deceased,"},{"time":503928,"text":"and, by extension, the deceased's family."},{"time":507220,"text":"So at funerals, relationships are reconfirmed"},{"time":511348,"text":"but also transformed"},{"time":513661,"text":"in a ritual drama that highlights"},{"time":516301,"text":"the most salient feature about death in this place:"},{"time":520079,"text":"its impact on life and the relationships of the living."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525345,"text":"So all of this focus on death"},{"time":528160,"text":"doesn't mean that Torajans don't aspire"},{"time":530796,"text":"to the ideal of a long life."},{"time":533472,"text":"They engage in many practices"},{"time":535541,"text":"thought to confer good health"},{"time":537669,"text":"and survival to an advanced age."},{"time":540533,"text":"But they don't put much stock"},{"time":542700,"text":"in efforts to prolong life in the face of debilitating illness"},{"time":547699,"text":"or in old age."},{"time":550354,"text":"It's said in Toraja that everybody has"},{"time":552217,"text":"sort of a predetermined amount of life."},{"time":554954,"text":"It's called the sunga'."},{"time":556932,"text":"And like a thread, it should be allowed to unspool"},{"time":560000,"text":"to its natural end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562940,"text":"So by having death as a part"},{"time":565488,"text":"of the cultural and social fabric of life,"},{"time":569657,"text":"people's everyday decisions about their health"},{"time":572630,"text":"and healthcare are affected."},{"time":575931,"text":"The patriarch of my husband's maternal clan,"},{"time":579058,"text":"Nenet Katcha,"},{"time":581130,"text":"is now approaching the age of 100, as far as we can tell."},{"time":586783,"text":"And there are increasing signs"},{"time":588885,"text":"that he is about to depart on his own journey for Puya."},{"time":593528,"text":"And his death will be greatly mourned."},{"time":598459,"text":"But I know that my husband's family"},{"time":600675,"text":"looks forward to the moment"},{"time":602893,"text":"when they can ritually display"},{"time":606550,"text":"what his remarkable presence has meant to their lives,"},{"time":611283,"text":"when they can ritually recount"},{"time":613021,"text":"his life's narrative,"},{"time":615036,"text":"weaving his story"},{"time":616800,"text":"into the history of their community."},{"time":620822,"text":"His story is their story."},{"time":624654,"text":"His funeral songs will sing them a song about themselves."},{"time":630426,"text":"And it's a story that has no discernible beginning,"},{"time":634211,"text":"no foreseeable end."},{"time":636832,"text":"It's a story that goes on"},{"time":638768,"text":"long after his body no longer does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643420,"text":"People ask me if I'm frightened or repulsed"},{"time":647940,"text":"by participating in a culture"},{"time":650660,"text":"where the physical manifestations of death"},{"time":653331,"text":"greet us at every turn."},{"time":655110,"text":"But I see something profoundly transformative"},{"time":658340,"text":"in experiencing death as a social process"},{"time":661755,"text":"and not just a biological one."},{"time":665011,"text":"In reality, the relationship between the living and the dead"},{"time":669075,"text":"has its own drama in the U.S. healthcare system,"},{"time":672365,"text":"where decisions about how long to stretch"},{"time":674908,"text":"the thread of life are made based on our emotional"},{"time":678181,"text":"and social ties with the people around us,"},{"time":680806,"text":"not just on medicine's ability to prolong life."},{"time":685925,"text":"We, like the Torajans,"},{"time":688650,"text":"base our decisions about life"},{"time":691445,"text":"on the meanings and the definitions"},{"time":695093,"text":"that we ascribe to death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697357,"text":"So I'm not suggesting that anyone in this audience"},{"time":700900,"text":"should run out and adopt the traditions"},{"time":703132,"text":"of the Torajans."},{"time":704754,"text":"It might be a little bit difficult"},{"time":706346,"text":"to put into play in the United States."},{"time":709680,"text":"But I want to ask what we can gain"},{"time":711561,"text":"from seeing physical death not only as a biological process"},{"time":716000,"text":"but as part of the greater human story."},{"time":720492,"text":"What would it be like to look on"},{"time":723023,"text":"the expired human form with love"},{"time":726472,"text":"because it's so intimately a part of who we all are?"},{"time":730196,"text":"If we could expand our definition of death"},{"time":733083,"text":"to encompass life,"},{"time":735494,"text":"we could experience death as part of life"},{"time":739408,"text":"and perhaps face death"},{"time":741670,"text":"with something other than fear."},{"time":746133,"text":"Perhaps one of the answers to the challenges"},{"time":749076,"text":"that are facing the U.S. healthcare system,"},{"time":751929,"text":"particularly in the end-of-life care,"},{"time":754355,"text":"is as simple as a shift in perspective,"},{"time":757385,"text":"and the shift in perspective in this case"},{"time":759402,"text":"would be to look at the social life of every death."},{"time":765030,"text":"It might help us recognize that the way we limit"},{"time":768515,"text":"our conversation about death"},{"time":770191,"text":"to something that's medical or biological"},{"time":773226,"text":"is reflective of a larger culture that we all share"},{"time":777049,"text":"of avoiding death, being afraid of talking about it."},{"time":782699,"text":"If we could entertain and value"},{"time":787139,"text":"other kinds of knowledge about life,"},{"time":790262,"text":"including other definitions of death,"},{"time":793936,"text":"it has the potential to change the discussions"},{"time":796138,"text":"that we have about the end of life."},{"time":799885,"text":"It could change the way that we die,"},{"time":803978,"text":"but more importantly,"},{"time":805990,"text":"it could transform the way that we live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813101,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}